    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**32.5 E2 Wave equation, Two first timesteps**

Suppose that \\\( u = u(x, t) \\\) satisfies the wave equation \\\( u_{tt} = c^2 u_{xx} \\\) in \\\( t > 0 \\\) and \\\( 0 < x < {@L@} \\\).

It is given that \\\( u \\\) satisfies the boundary conditions \\\( u(0, t) = u(1, t) = 0 \\\) for \\\( t > 0 \\\). The initial elevation may be summarized as

{@apply(table,append([[float(x_i),f_i]],args(transpose(matrix(x,f)))))@}

and the string is initially at rest (that is, \\\( g(x) = 0 \\\)). The application is such that the wave speed \\\( c = {@c@} \\\).

Carry out the first two time-steps of the numerical method

\\\[
u_j^{n+1} = 2u_j^n - u_j^{n-1} + \mu^2 \left(u_{j+1}^n - 2u_j^n + u_{j-1}^n \right)
\\\]

where \\\( \mu = \frac{c \, \delta t}{\delta x} \\\), with \\\( \delta x = {@dx@} \\\) and \\\( \delta t = {@dt@} \\\).

\\\(\mu=\\\) [[input:S_mu]] [[validation:S_mu]] [[feedback:mu]]

Grid point values at \\\(t=\delta t\\\) with at least 3 s.f.

